item.title: 8 years of trials and errors…
item.description: At 32, I had enough of being the big guy. I weighed 500lbs and I wanted more from life. That meant less of everything that I thought made me happy. It was extremely difficult and I have relapsed a few times but it’s all part of the journey. I quit drinking alcohol and soda. I quit smoking pot and cigarettes. I quit eating out and started waking more. I did get gastric bypass but at 35, I gained all the weight back and had to loose it all over again. Forgiving myself was very difficult but necessary to move on. Im now 208lbs and the past year I’ve been working on a slow bulk. This is still all new to me so progress is slow but obviously you can see the results! Here’s a link if you want to read a little more about my story. https://www.youembody.com/connections/support-network-weight-loss-accountability

item.title: Epstein's 2008 Plea Deal - He turns himself in, so his pedo-ring won't be investigated by the FBI
item.description: https://www.miamiherald.com/news/local/article220097825.html TLDR - Federal prosecutor Alexander Acosta struck a plea agreement hiding the extent of Epstein's crimes and ending an FBI investigation into whether there were more victims or more powerful people who took part. It has been called the "Deal of the Century" or a "Sweetheart Deal" Acosta was told by the Bush Administration told him to "leave it alone" because Epstein "belonged to intelligence" and was "above his paygrade." https://observer.com/2019/07/jeffrey-epstein-spy-intelligence-work/ https://www.thedailybeast.com/jeffrey-epsteins-sick-story-played-out-for-years-in-plain-sight/ Acosta resigned in July 2019 over the scandal, though he defended his actions as guaranteeing at last some jail time for Epstein. Since 2008, Epstein had been listed as a level three on the New York sex offenders register. It was a lifelong designation meaning he was considered to be at a high risk of reoffending. But Epstein maintained his properties and his assets after his conviction. After 3+1⁄2 months, He was allowed to leave the jail on "work release" for up to twelve hours a day, six days a week. This contravened the sheriff's own policies requiring a maximum remaining sentence of ten months and making sex offenders ineligible for the privilege. He was allowed to come and go outside of specified release hours. During this time, he would continue to run his child sex trafficking ring. https://www.miamiherald.com/news/local/article219494920.html In light of all the new information from the leaked files, this, this has me more pissed than anything else This was a miscarriage of justice! We could have ended it all, right then and there and removed these sick fucks from society. Instead they gave Esptein a plea deal, which included not investigating his clients and accomplices.. I don't care how powerful or influential these people are, they should all be in a cell or worse for the rest of their disgusting lives. Always always FUCK TRUMP RELEASE THE UNREDACTED EPSTEIN FILES
